data.content:
The most likely cause is that you never set the page's **`BindingContext`** to your ViewModel. Without it, the bindings have nothing to resolve against.

**Fix — set the BindingContext**, e.g. in the code-behind constructor:

```csharp
public MyPage()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = new MyViewModel();
}
```

If you're already setting `BindingContext`, the second thing to check is that your ViewModel implements **`INotifyPropertyChanged`** and raises `PropertyChanged` when property values change after construction. Using `ObservableProperty` from the MAUI Community Toolkit (or `[ObservableProperty]` from CommunityToolkit.Mvvm) handles this automatically.
